        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "$validator = new Zend_Validate_Int();\n$value = '23';\nif ($validator->isValid($value)) {\n    echo('ok');\n} else {\n    echo('not ok');\n}\n\n$validator = new Zend_Validate_Int(\"en_NZ\");\n$value = '23';\nif ($validator->isValid($value)) {\n    echo('ok');\n} else {\n    echo('not ok');\n}\n\nin the both  samples return \"ok\", but in the second sample ignores a user locale parameter (en_NZ).\nI can attach a Xdebug trace file is necessary. \n\nSolution:\n\n...\n    public function __construct($locale = null)\n    {\n        $this->setLocale($locale);\n    }\n...\n    public function setLocale($locale = null)\n    {\n\n\t\tif (!is_null($locale)) {\n\t        require_once 'Zend\/Locale.php';\n    \t    $this->_locale = Zend_Locale::findLocale($locale);\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t$this->_locale = $locale;\n\t\t}\n        return $this;\n    }\n..."
        },
